  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nWhen specifying multiple services using the `service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-extra-security-groups` annotation the SG defined in that annotation may be the one used for ingress to the instances. If this happens for multiple service ELBs and one of those services is removed then the rule may be removed during clean up causing the other ELBs losing the ability to contact their instances.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nRemoval of any service should not lead to disruption of other services.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\n1. Create a security group in AWS.\r\n2. Create multiple services referencing that SG in `service.beta.kubernetes.io/aws-load-balancer-extra-security-groups`.\r\n3. Remove one of those services.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8.8\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: AWS\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): 4.4.121-k8s",
